column1: #Text=It is a suburb of Amsterdam in an area that used to be known as Nieuwer-Amstel until 1964 .
#Text=Amstelveen , known as Nieuwer-Amstel until 1964 , is a city in the Amstelland .
#Text=The city grew from a town founded for the harvesting of bog , which was a popular fuel at the time .
#Text=During the seventeenth and eighteenth century , wealthy Amsterdammers moved to the town in search of some peace and quiet .
#Text=Originally , Southern Amsterdam was a part of the municipality .
#Text=After annexation of Amsterdam Zuid , the former town hall of Nieuwer-Amstel housed the Amsterdam city archives from 1914 to 2007 .
#Text=Not late after the first annexation , in 1921 , another annexation followed taking away the northern and most densely populated part of Amstelveen .
#Text=This left the municipality to conclude of the town of Amstelveen as well as several small towns .
#Text=Amstelveen , however , kept its appeal to the wealthier citizens of Amsterdam , which shows from the suburbs built around 1930 in the northwest of the municipality .

#Text=After the Second World War , Nieuwer-Amstel became an overflow for Amsterdam , housing more and more people that could not find or did not want a home in Amsterdam , as well as people that worked at the growing Schiphol Airport .
#Text=During the 1960s Amstelveen was even the largest growing city of the Netherlands .
#Text=In 1964 the municipality was renamed after the city that by now was considered an extension of Amsterdam .
#Text=Since the last half of the 1990s , Amstelveen 's expansion has become more and more gradual .
#Text=At this time , no further expansion is planned .
#Text=The most recent expansion is Westwijk to the southwest of town .
#Text=To suit the needs of the already existing population , the Stadshart has been created to replace the former town centre .
#Text=Here you will find a central library , large mall , as well as cultural and gastronomical services and offices .
#Text=In 2003 Amstelveen was named Most attractive city of the Netherlands for its proximity to the nation 's capital Amsterdam , its safety , accessibility and richness of culture .
#Text=The A9 crosses straight through the municipality and functions as a ring-road for traffic that does not need to go to Amsterdam per se .
#Text=Amstelveen can be reached from The Hague , Rotterdam and Leiden using the A4 followed by the A9 once having passed by Schiphol .
#Text=, Den Bosch and Eindhoven can use the A2 , followed by the A9 after passing by Abcoude .
#Text=and everything north there of is best off using the A1 , followd by a kilometre of A2 heading away from Amsterdam , quickly followed by the A9 .
#Text=Amstelveen has a direct connection to the central station of Amsterdam via line 51 of the Amsterdam Metro .
#Text=The metro has many stops in Amstelveen .
#Text=Tram line 5 terminates at Binnenhof , which is several metres away from Amstelveen Centrum .

#Text=Busses also run from the central busstation to Aalsmeer ( line 171 and 357 ) , Uithoorn ( line 174 and 374 ) , Haarlem ( line 300 and 356 ) , Amsterdam Bijlmer ArenA ( line 356 ) and Amsterdam Centraal ( line 347 and 357 ) .
#Text=Amstelveen 's city centre is navigable on foot , with metro line connecting to most of the city that cannot be reached easily by foot .
#Text=Buslines 165 , 166 and 167 serve as city busses , connecting all of the city with the central bus hub near the Amstelveen Centrum metro station .
#Text=, Amsterdamseweg 104a ( Corner of Molenweg and Amsterdamseweg ) , ☏ +31206433333 .
#Text=Windmill , which serves as a restaurant now .
#Text=A larger forest/park that straddles the border between Amstelveen and Amsterdam .
#Text=Horse rental , canoe rental and an open air theater are some of the attractions .
#Text=The collection of the museum consists of key works by artists of the movements Vrij Beelden ( 1945 ) , Cobra ( 1948 – 1951 ) , and Creatie ( 1950 – 1955 ) .
#Text=A modern visual art museum , which was established in 1991 by Jan van der Togt , an industrialist and founder of the company Tomado who was a collector of contemporary art .
#Text=P60 offers an audience to up and coming pop artists , as well as already established artists , whether they are Dutch or not .
